a.xlink:title: Role of a party in an activity.
Role played by a party in a system.
Member of an exchange's clearing corporation, responsible for executing client trades and involved in the clearing of trades.
Type of entity that plays a specific role in a specific context.

Person to be contacted in a given organisation. In the corporate action domain (including meeting notifications) , it is the contact person at the party organising the meeting, at the issuer or at an intermediary.
Calculation of the exposure amount that one party has vis-a-vis one counterparty or a central system, based on its credit risk.
Posting to an account that results in an increase or decrease to a balance.
Set of integrated applications that provides centralised services such as clearing, netting, reconciliation, trading and/or settlement.

Unique and unambiguous identifier for a clearing system member, as assigned by the clearing system. In some clearing systems, the accounts of the clearing system members are also assigned an identifier. The identifier can be used when transmitting, reconciling and confirming payment orders or security transfer instructions prior to settlement, and may include the netting of instructions and the establishment of final positions for settlement.
Account to or from which a securities entry is made.

Record of transactions in specific types of assets, maintained by a servicing party on behalf of one or more owning parties. Business relationship between an account servicer and one or more account owners.
